@rhatdan No it does not work. Now tls-verify always defaults to true not matter what I pass as argument.

my-ubuntu is an insecure registry, the first command should fail to find the image.

```bash
[kkoukiou@sequoia cockpit-podman]$ sudo varlink call unix:/run/podman/io.podman/io.podman.SearchImage '{"name": "my-ubuntu", "tlsVerify": true}'
{
  "images": [
    {
      "description": "",
      "is_automated": false,
